    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs required 3) is accepted given that the single ASTM F1717 configuration represents the regulatory worst case and is consistent with industry practice for pedicle screw submissions. Overall credibility is judged sufficient for Medium model risk and Medium decision consequence. The FEA framework is accepted for use in the 510(k) submission.",
